server creation = nodejs + Express
----------------------------------

Basic Commands
--------------

1)creation of package.json --npm init
2)creqation of the node modules --npm i express 
3)
4)
5)install mongos-npm i mongos


Basic Steps
-----------
1)Creating a folder (Bankserver)
2)Create package.json
3)Install express
4)Create index.js
5)Import express inside the index.js
6)Create an app using the express
7)Setup port number
8)Resolving HTTP request
      Get- TO get the data
      Psot- TO post the data
      Put- update data partially
      Patch- update data completely
      delete- to delete data completely



9)HTTP response code
     1XX-- information
     2XX-- successful
     3XX-- redirection
     4XX-- client error
     5XX-- server error





10) JWT Token
    install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
    to generate a token-sign()


11)Middleware
    it come in the middle of the request and response cycle of the nodejs execution process
     1)Application specific middleware - for entire application
     req,res,next
     2)Router specific middleware-validate token - verify()-jwtwebtoken


12)Database Integration
    1)install mongos-npm i mongos




13)Asynchronous functon resolving - promise

  1)Resolve State-then()
  2)Reject state-catch()



14)CORS - cross origin resources sharing 
   
   istall cors- npm i core


   port 4200 (angular)-----request---->3000(node)(recieve)



15)Asynchronous call-RxJs-(Reactive Extension fo javascript)

JS-promise
TS-RxJs(library)

    1)observable
     a)resolved-subscribe()
     b)reject-catch
     